docs.summary:
Money.
 Default format to use. Sufficiently compliant with majority of standards: w3c, ISO 4217, ISO 20022, ISO 8583:2003.

members.name: value
members.doc: Monetary amount. Decimal string with a period as a decimal separator (e.g., 3.99). Optionally, a single (-), to indicate that the amount is negative.

members.name: currency
members.doc: Currency code. Must be valid ISO 4217 currency code (e.g., USD).

members.name: formattedValue
members.doc: Monetary amount. Decimal string in local format (e.g., 1 000,30). Optionally, a single (-), to indicate that the amount is negative.

members.name: createdDate
members.doc:
The date when balance record was paid out.
 This only applies to payouts that have already occurred and not those that are scheduled.

members.doc: The date when balance record was instantly available.

members.name: release

docs.summary:
A balance record reflects either funds being added or deducted from a Wix Payments balance.
 This can result from a charge, refund, chargeback, chargeback or refund reversal, or a reserve.
 Note: In certain cases Balance Record can be "virtual" - it's not physically created yet, but will be created at some point of time in future.
 Such records have no "id" and "applied_date"

members.name: accountProfileId
members.doc: Account profile balance record belongs to.

members.doc: This corresponds with the amount of the balance record.

members.name: fee
members.doc: This reflects the fee that Wix Payments collects from each balance record.

members.name: net

members.doc:
Fields to return in response, supported values: "scheduled", "processing",
 "funds_on_hold", "payouts_under_minimum_amount", "negative", "reserve", "blocked", "modal"

docs.summary:
Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • CARD
  • CARD_READER
  • ACH
  • APPLE_PAY
  • BOLETO
  • GIROPAY
  • IDEAL
  • PIX
  • SEPA
  • SOFORT
  • PAY_PAL
  • TAP_TO_PAY
  • GOOGLE_PAY
  • AFFIRM
  • AFTERPAY
  • KLARNA

Type of balance record Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • CREDIT - Credit
  • REFUND - Refund
  • CHARGEBACK - Chargeback
  • REFUND_REVERSAL - Refund reversal.
  • CHARGEBACK_REVERSAL - Chargeback reveral.
  • RESERVE_HOLD - Reserve hold.
  • RESERVE_RELEASE - Reserve Release.
  • TOPUP - TOP-UP
  • CREDIT_FAILED - Credit failed
  • CHARGEBACK_FEE - Chargeback fee
  • CHARGEBACK_FEE_REVERSAL - Chargeback fee reversal

Status of balance record. Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • PENDING_CREDIT - This refers to any balance records that have not yet been added to the Available Balance.
  • CREDITED - This refers to any balance records that have been added to the Available Balance.
  • RESERVED - This refers to any balance record that has been reserved from a payout.
  • PENDING_DEBIT - This refers to any balance records that have been deducted from the Available Balance.
  • DEBITED - This refers to any balance records that have been deducted from the Available Balance.
  • PAID_OUT - Balance records that are *not* of type:Refund or type:Chargeback that are included in the payout.
  • DEDUCTED_FROM_PAYOUT - Balance record that are of type:Refund or type:Chargeback that are included in the payout.
  • PAYOUT_REVERSED - Balance record was paid out but payout failed.

tag or "named-filter" for the balance records Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • AVAILABLE - Query records available for payout
  • PENDING - Query pending records
  • RESERVE - Query reserve records
  • ESTIMATED_RESERVE_HOLD - Query estimated reserve hold records Note: First record returned in list/query methods would be virtual (calculated on a fly, based on exiting account balance)
  • ESTIMATED_RESERVE_RELEASE - Query estimated reserve release records Note: First record returned in list/query methods would be virtual (calculated on a fly, based on exiting account balance)
  • RESERVE_RELEASED - Query reserve released records
  • PENDING_TOPUP - Query pending top up records
  • PAID_OUT - Query paid out records
  • NOT_PAID_OUT - Query all not paid out records

`NullValue` is a singleton enumeration to represent the null value for the `Value` type union. The JSON representation for `NullValue` is JSON `null`. Possible values are:
  • NULL_VALUE - Null value.
